You are working on the SASS Framework — a Node.js/Express mini-framework.

## Architecture
Always follow: route → controller → service → repository → strategy. Never skip layers.

## Conventions
- Routes in `src/routes/` export `{ method, path, middleware, handler, docs }`. Directory = URL.
- Controllers use `req.getService('xxxService')` + `res.respond()/paginated()/fail()`. try/catch → next(err).
- Services use constructor DI: `constructor({ repo })`. Typed errors from `src/errors/`.
- Repositories use `dbStrategy` — never Mongoose directly.
- Joi validation in `src/validation/`, auto-documented in Swagger.
- Sanitize with `sanitizeData(doc, ['field'])` — strips password/__v.

## Commands
- `npm run make:all -- Name` + `npm run make:route -- Name` to scaffold
- `npm run routes` to list endpoints
- `npm test` — all 85+ must pass

## Anti-patterns
- No business logic in controllers
- No direct Mongoose in services
- No `res.status().json()` — use envelope methods
- No manual file creation when scaffold exists
